column1: #Text=And make him Phœbus like his throne\r
#Text=May prove the ruine of a land\r
#Text=Unlesse great Jove downe from the skye\r
#Text=Strike with his hand that cannot err\r
#Text=And cure though Phœbus greive our woe\r
#Text=From such a face that cann worke soe\r
#Text=From Jobs false frends that would entice\r
#Text=His frownes more then his makers fearing\r
#Text=Such for which old Eve was chidden\r
#Text=From bread of Laborers sweat, and toyle\r
#Text=The milke of Babells proud whore duggs\r
#Text=From wyne that can destroye the braine\r
#Text=And from the daingerous figg of Spaine\r
#Text=From prick of Conscience such a sting\r
#Text=As staines the Soule, heavens blesse my King\r
#Text=From such a tribe as may with drawe\r
#Text=From such a smooth, and beardlesse Chinn\r
#Text=As may provoke, or tempt to sinn\r
#Text=From such a hand whose moyst palme may\r
#Text=My soveraigne lead out of the way\r
#Text=From what may sett his Soule a reeling\r
#Text=Such damn’d perfumes are fitt for hell\r
#Text=Let noe such scent his nostrills staine\r
#Text=From smells that poyson may the braine\r
#Text=Heavens still preserve him, Next I crave\r
#Text=Thou wilt be pleas’d great God to save\r
#Text=Whose whoreish breath hath power to lead\r
#Text=O lett such lipps be never kist\r
#Text=That thou wilt take the Filme away\r
#Text=That keepes my Soveraignes eyes from vieweing\r
#Text=Then lett him Heare good God the sounds\r
#Text=Aswell of Men, as of his hounds\r
#Text=Give him a Taste and tymely too\r
#Text=Give him a Feelinge of there woes\r
#Text=Whose blacke deeds have ecclips’t his worth.
#Text=These found, and scourg’d for their offences\r
#Text=Heavens blesse my Soveraigne, and his sences.
